The '''Filthy Thievin' Bastards''' is an alternative punk group formed in 2000 in . The band was originally a side project put together by  and Darius Koski of the .  (also from Swingin' Utters) later joined the band, along with  from .
Their music is influenced by , celtic rock, and the Utters style of street punk.  The project's first (short) album, ''Our Fathers Sent Us'', was release by  in 2000. In 2001, the band released ''A Melody of Retreads and Broken Quills'' on . The next album ''My Pappy Was a Pistol'' was released in 2005. In March 2007 Filthy Thievin' Bastards released their next album ''... and I'm A Son of a Gun'' on .  The naming of the last two albums was a nod to American Singer/Songwriter .